        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:24PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Allison, or near Eutaw, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eutaw, Greensboro, Forkland, Akron, Boligee, Union, Walden Quarters,
Thornhill, Arcola, Wedgeworth, Tishabee, Greensboro Municipal
Airport, Allison, Duffys Bend, Bluffport, Sawyerville, Evansville,
Belmont, Eutaw Municipal Airport, and Birdine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
